Ex-Afghan president Najibullah's mother killed in Peshawar 
The mother of former Afghan president Najibullah was killed in a road
accident here Sunday, police said.
Bibi Haleema, 70, who had been living here with her son-in-law, was hit
by a bus while she was crossing a road, according to the police.
Najibullah has been holed up in a UN building in Kabul since his
overthrow in April 1992.
